The paper deals with the design of efficient solutions for abstract argumentation problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Answer-Set Programming (ASP) is a prominent approach in this field, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also presents new encodings for argumentation semantics, which could be relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses benchmarks, which could be related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
